# DASieve

DAS (Distributed Acoustic Sensing) processing, QC and phase-picking pipeline
built on [dascore](https://dascore.org).

## Install

```bash
# installs everything (processing, QC, all pickers including the DL backends)
pip install -e .

# PhaseNet-DAS additionally needs the vendored EQNet submodule:
git submodule update --init --recursive
```

Requires Python >= 3.10.

## Usage

```python
import dascore as dc
import dasieve as sieve

patch = dc.spool("event.h5")[0].select(distance=(0, 3000))
patch = sieve.processing.to_strain_rate(patch)
patch = sieve.processing.decimate(patch, target_fs=500, target_dx=5)
patch = sieve.processing.cmd_remove(patch, dim="distance", window=5000)

# pickers (all return the shared PICK_COLUMNS schema, persisted to a SQLite catalog)
sieve.picker.trigger_picker(patch, method="ar", file_name="event.h5")
sieve.picker.phasenet_picker(patch, min_prob=0.3, file_name="event.h5")   # EQNet 2-D PhaseNet-DAS
sieve.picker.seisbench_picker(patch, model="eqtransformer", file_name="event.h5")
```

## Package layout

| Submodule            | Purpose                                              |
|----------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| `dasieve.processing` | `to_strain_rate`, `decimate`, `cmd_remove`           |
| `dasieve.qc`         | `compute_psd`, `plot_patch`                           |
| `dasieve.picker`     | `trigger_picker`, `phasenet_picker`, `seisbench_picker` |
| `dasieve.catalog`    | SQLite pick catalog (`save_picks`, `load_picks`)     |
| `dasieve.geometry`   | survey geometry attachment                           |
| `dasieve.watcher`    | directory watcher for streaming ingest               |
